  "instructions": [
    "Roast the garlic by wrapping it in foil and baking at 400°F for 30 minutes.",
    "Sauté the onion, ginger, and cayenne pepper in olive oil until softened.",
    "Add the peanuts, paprika, peanut butter, salt, and pepper to the sautéed mixture.",
    "Stir in the vinegar and let it simmer for 10 minutes.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a clay tagine and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.",
    "Serve the Roasted Garlic German Peanut Tagine hot, garnished with fresh herbs.",
    "Reheat the peanut brittle in the oven for 2 minutes to melt slightly.",
    "Crush the peanut brittle into crumbs and sprinkle over the tagine.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
